<title>JAPAN: Japan Energy falls on larger loss forecast.</title>
<headline>Japan Energy falls on larger loss forecast.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Japan Energy Corp fell sharply on Wednesday, depressed by the company's larger loss estimate for the year that ended on March 31, traders said.</p>
<p>The share was down 48 yen at 259 yen by 0130 GMT making it the largest percentage loser on the first section of the bourse.</p>
<p>Turnover was 1,854,000 shares.</p>
